news.title: Bengaluru: 40,000 apply for '1 lakh housing scheme'
news.para: The scheme envisages building 1 lakh houses in Bengaluru Urban district — in multiple locations spread across Anekal, KR Puram, Dasarahalli, Byatarayanapura, Mahadevapura, Yelahanka and Yeshwantpur — in phases.

news.title: Affordable housing finance companies' loan book to grow 17-20% in FY23: Study
news.para: As on December 31, 2021, the total loan book of AHFCs stood at Rs 66,221 crore and constituted about 6 per cent of the overall housing finance companies (HFCs) loan book.

news.title: Home First Finance reports 54% jump in profit to Rs 48 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income during January-March quarter of 2021-22 rose by 15 per cent to Rs 156 crore as against Rs 136 crore in the same period of 2020-21, Home First Finance said in a release.

news.title: SC ruling on retro effect of Benami Law keenly awaited
news.para: A plethora of transactions like cash transfers, property deals, and share issuances have come under the lens with the invocation of the Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Amendment Act, which came into effect from November 1, 2016 following the amendment of a 28-year-old ineffective law.

news.title: Godrej Properties to add over 10 housing projects to development portfolio in FY23
news.para: These new additions will be made through its existing model of forming alliances and even direct land acquisitions supported by its robust balance sheet.

news.title: Land set to become costlier in Greater Noida
news.para: The allotment rates of residential plots have been increased by 15% to 26% — land was priced between Rs 24,000 per sqmt and Rs 33,300 per sqmt earlier, but will now cost Rs 34,000 per sqmt to Rs 39,000 per sqmt.

news.title: H-RERA purview extends even to occupancy certificates before Act, says HC
news.para: ​Division bench comprising Justice Amol Rattan Singh and Justice Lalit Batra of the HC has passed these orders while hearing a petition filed by Experion Developers Private Limited.

news.title: Godrej Properties posts profit of Rs 352 crore in FY22
news.para: Mumbai-based Godrej Properties posted a net profit of Rs 352.37 crore during the 2021-22 fiscal year as against a net loss of Rs 189.30 crore in the previous year.

news.title: Haryana RERA issue arrest warrants against Ansal Housing Corporation directors
news.para: "To reiterate the probity and responsibility of obeying and respecting the rules framed for better and smooth functioning of the real estate sector, stringent actions are taken against culprits," said KK Khandelwal, chairman, Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority.

news.title: Chennai development body to increase FSI of buildings along major roads
news.para: As of now, the maximum FSI for a high rise building in the city is 3.25. This is expected to go up to 4.875 using premium FSI of 50% that will cost builders more.The CMDA amendment will allow a free FSI increase between 6 and 8.

news.title: Goa: FIR filed against builder for Arpora hill-cutting
news.para: NGPDA assistant engineer Vikram Tengse, in his complaint to Anjuna police station, said the authority has given development permission under Section 44 for construction of commercial block 1 and 2 (hotel project) and proposed residential villas (1 to 18 numbers) in Survey No 157/1-A of Arpora village to IAPL.

news.title: Nagpur: With three days notice, NIT razes 35 shops before businesses shift into mall
news.para: ​Then, even before the deadline ended to shift his business to a shop in the mall, a team of civic officials, policemen, and staffers of the mall builder — Pune-based Goel Ganga Infrastructure and Real Estate Private Ltd — demolished the shop on Monday morning, causing huge financial loss to Gala.

news.title: Hyderabad's new master plan to cover 84 villages of GO 111
news.para: The new master plan will bring 84 villages that came under GO 111, catchment areas of Himayatsagar and Osmansagar reservoirs under its ambit.

news.title: Nod to gates with night-vision cameras at seven licensed colonies in Gurugram
news.para: These colonies are Ardee City B Block, DLF phases I, II & V, blocks C of Sushant Lok I, II & III. Another colony, Experion Society in Sector 112, which also sought permission for installing gates, has, however, been refused the same.

news.title: Jaipur: 1,327 lease deeds sanctioned on first day of Shahar camp
news.para: On the first day, the civic body issued a total of 1327 lease deeds to the plot owners. As per the records, 1102 free hold lease deeds and 225 lease deeds were issued on May 2.
